NO VULNERABILITIES FOUND for path traversal / symlink / TOCTOU / injection vectors. The implementation correctly uses realpath + prefix checks and passes the resolved path downstream.

FINDING 1: MEDIUM env-controlled allow-list roots
Description: _validate_project_path trusts AGENTPAAS_PROJECT_ROOT and $HOME without validation or sanitization. An attacker who can influence the process environment can set AGENTPAAS_PROJECT_ROOT=/ or HOME=/etc to make arbitrary paths (including /etc) appear allowed.
Proof: 
- AGENTPAAS_PROJECT_ROOT=/ → project_root realpaths to /; any resolved path under / matches the startswith rule.
- HOME=/etc → allowed_roots includes /etc; paths under it pass.
Existing tests mock the env but never test malicious values.
Fix recommendation: Validate/sanitize AGENTPAAS_PROJECT_ROOT and HOME before use (reject absolute roots outside expected safe set, or require explicit allow-list of roots independent of env). Add tests that attempt these overrides and assert rejection.

All 12 listed attack vectors are mitigated except the two env-root cases above (vectors 3 and 12), which are the only realistic bypasses of the allow-list claim. The symlink test already present (test_reject_symlink_escape) plus realpath usage covers chain/symlink cases; the .. check after realpath plus prefix check covers traversal cases; callers always use the captured resolved value (no TOCTOU on the path string itself).

